## Per-milestone shape

Each milestone has:

- **Goal** — one paragraph stating what this milestone delivers.
- **Checklist** — `- [ ]` items, each a discrete deliverable.
- **Exit criteria** — one sentence stating what "done" means. Read it before starting; if you can't write a clear exit criterion, the milestone is too vague.
- **Kill criteria** (optional) — one sentence: "if this turns out to be true, stop and re-plan." Use for milestones with genuine uncertainty.

When a milestone closes, mark with `✅ (date, shipped at vX.Y.Z)` so the roadmap ties to release tags.
